    management: "Quality control: positive and negative controls required. Molecular weight markers for sizing. Modern replacements: PCR/sequencing for DNA analysis, RT-qPCR for RNA, ELISA/mass spectrometry for protein. Western blot for HIV replaced by 4th-generation Ag/Ab combo immunoassay + HIV-1/2 differentiation immunoassay.",
    complications: "Labor-intensive, time-consuming (1-2 days), requires significant technical skill. Non-specific binding can cause false bands. Probe hybridization conditions (stringency) critical for specificity.",
